Zephyr platform: don't add an mbedTLS entropy source under CHIP_CRYPTO_PSA.

With chip_crypto="psa" the PAL's add_entropy_source() is a stub that
returns CHIP_ERROR_UNSUPPORTED_CHIP_FEATURE (PSA owns its RNG; on
Zephyr 4.4 it is CONFIG_MBEDTLS_PSA_CRYPTO_EXTERNAL_RNG backed by the
hardware TRNG csprng driver). PlatformManagerImpl::_InitChipStack()
only skips the call for NRF_SECURITY or the mbedTLS entropy-glue
Kconfigs, none of which exist in this configuration, so InitChipStack()
fails at boot with 0x6C. Gate the entropy-source block on
!CHIP_CRYPTO_PSA as well.

Upstream candidate: yes (any generic-Zephyr PSA build hits this).

